data.title: Elections in Estonia
data.text:
Parliamentary Elections, 5 March 2023

Following an invitation to observe the early general elections scheduled for 5 March 2023, based on the findings and conclusions of the Needs Assessment Mission conducted between 10 and 13 January 2023, and in accordance with its mandate, ODIHR has deployed an Election Expert Team (EET) for these

More info...

Parliamentary Elections, 3 March 2019

Following an invitation from the authorities of Estonia, and based on the findings and conclusions of a Needs Assessment Mission (NAM), ODIHR has deployed an Election Expert Team (EET) for the 3 March parliamentary elections.

More info...

Parliamentary Elections, 1 March 2015

Following an official invitation from the government of Estonia, and based on the findings and conclusions of a Needs Assessment Mission (NAM), the OSCE/ODIHR has deployed an Election Expert Team (EET) for the 1 March parliamentary elections.

More info...

Parliamentary Elections, 6 March 2011

Following an invitation from the Estonian authorities, ODIHR established an election assessment mission for the parliamentary elections on 6 March.

More info...

Parliamentary Elections, 4 March 2007

In response to an invitation from Estonia's Foreign Minister, ODIHR deployed an election assessment mission for the parliamentary elections on 4 March
